    "body": "### Description\n\nHi\n\n```\nNVIM v0.12.0-nightly+16495e6\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1741730670\n``` \n\nAnd in https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-eslint/blob/6d61063d2f7361e728a1968d7a3fd4edb41acd16/server/src/eslint.ts#L925\n\n```typescript\nconst eslintPath = settings.experimental?.useFlatConfig ? 'eslint/use-at-your-own-risk' : 'eslint';\n```\nIn https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/44acfe887d4056f704ccc4f17513ed41c9e2b2e6/lsp/eslint.lua#L196\n\nWe always set the config to true if there is a flat config file (like `eslint.config.js`)\n\nIn [Flat config rollout plans - ESLint - Pluggable JavaScript Linter](https://eslint.org/blog/2023/10/flat-config-rollout-plans/#eslintrc-removed-in-eslint-v10.0.0) (emphasis mine):\n\n> For API users, you’ll need to stop using the classes from the /use-at-your-own-risk entrypoint. The API in v10.0.0 will change in the following ways:\n>\n>    The ESLint class will now be the only way to interact with the core.\n>    The LegacyESLint class will be removed.\n>    **The FlatESLint class will be removed.**\n>    The shouldUseFlatConfig() method will always return true.\n>    The Linter class configType constructor option will be invalid and throw an error.\n\nSee [fix: remove fake `FlatESLint` and `LegacyESLint` exports by fasttime · Pull Request #20460 · eslint/eslint](https://github.com/eslint/eslint/pull/20460)\n\nThe following error occurs in the `nvim/lsp.log`:\n\n```log\n[START][2026-02-18 13:18:09] LSP logging initiated\n[ERROR][2026-02-18 13:18:09] ...unwrapped-16495e6/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/log.lua:151\t\"The eslint library loaded from /home/neuromante/code/js/eslint10-test/node_modules/eslint/lib/unsupported-api.js doesn't export a FlatESLint class.\"\n```\n\nI think removing the setting is not enough, this will break eslint < 10 users using the flat config.\n\nCan we somehow check the eslint version before toggling the flag or should we handle this in our own configs?\n\nThanks",
