            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> is `useFlatConfig` something that is important or can we just drop it?\n\nAccording to what I could find in extension source code, it's relevant for ESLint versions before v8.57: https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-eslint/blob/6d61063d2f7361e728a1968d7a3fd4edb41acd16/server/src/eslint.ts#L978-L981\n\n<img width=\"1353\" height=\"105\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/30c4ccb5-5530-4d28-9cca-e1723fa90be2\" />\n\nTherefore, dropping this entirely would force people on older ESLint versions (v8.57 is almost exactly two years old[^npm-eslint]) to explicitly set `experimental.useFlatConfig = true` in their LSP configuration. I don't know if that's an acceptable tradeoff.\n\nOn the other hand, the way it's currently set up is also extremely limiting and blocks the way forward. Unconditionally setting `experimental.useFlatConfig = true` from `before_init` means that, as far as I understand, there is currently no way of forcing the setting to `false` without overriding the entire `before_init` callback.\n\n[^npm-eslint]:https://www.npmjs.com/package/eslint/v/8.57.0",
