            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "From what I'm reading in [the language server's README](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-eslint/blob/fc28cc4259a98a968d95360543fd0711a6f73057/README.md#version-305---pre-release), something like the following would work for the majority of users:\n\n```lua\n      local use_flat_config = config.settings.useFlatConfig\n      if\n        use_flat_config == nil\n        and config.settings.experimental\n        and config.settings.experimental.useFlatConfig ~= nil\n      then\n        use_flat_config = config.settings.experimental.useFlatConfig\n      end\n\n      if use_flat_config == nil then\n        -- Support flat config files\n        -- They contain 'config' in the file name\n        local flat_config_files = vim.tbl_filter(function(file)\n          return file:match('config')\n        end, eslint_config_files)\n\n        for _, file in ipairs(flat_config_files) do\n          ...\n\n          if #filterd_files > 0 then\n            config.settings.useFlatConfig = true\n            break\n          end\n        end\n      end\n```\n\nThis would allow users to explicitly set either `settings.useFlatConfig` or `settings.experimental.useFlatConfig` if they want to skip checking for flat config files and manually opt-in. This would mostly be relevant for users on eslint earlier than 8.57.0, but also for users still using `.eslintrc` with eslint `>= 8.57.0, < 10.0.0`.",
